"{\"uid\": \"nbcconnecticut.com-paris-2024-summer-olympics-michael-phelps-joins-nbcs-olympics-coverage-at-2024-paris-games-3318761\", \"text\": \"Michael Phelps tops the list of most decorated Olympians in history - and it's really not even close.  Out of the pool and into the broadcast booth once more.  That's right, 23-time gold medal-winning swimmerMichael Phelpsis returning to NBCUniversal this summer and heading to Paris to work both daytime and primetime coverage at the2024 Olympic Games.  Stream Connecticut News for free, 24/7, wherever you are.  Phelps, a 28-time Olympic medalist, is themost decorated athlete in the event's historyand previously offered insight for NBC during its coverage of the2020 Tokyo Olympics.  He will be providing swimming analysis live from Paris'La D\\u00e9fense Arenaonce the competition kicks off after theOpening Ceremonyon July 26.  Team USA looks to dominate in the pool once again this summer. How many medals can the Americans bring home from France?  \\\"We are excited to have Michael return to our coverage across both daytime and primetime, and of course, the place where no one knows more about winning - at the pool,\\\" said Molly Solomon, executive producer and president, NBC Olympics Production. \\\"With his ability to analyze and entertain, our viewers are in for another gold-medal performance.\\\"  Phelps started his broadcast duties a month early, joining Dan Hicks and Rowdy Gaines in the booth to watch the competition\\u00a0at theU.S. Swimming Trialsin Indianapolis Friday night.  In Paris, he will work alongside Hicks and Gaines during select swimming competitions. The team also features correspondent Elizabeth Beisel\\u00a0and\\u00a0reporter Melissa Stark at the swimming venue in Paris.  Phelpscame out of retirement at the 2016 Summer Olympicsin Brazil, where he served as Team USA's flag bearer during the Parade of Nations.  Phelps went back to his post-swimming career a month later in August 2016. At the time of his retirement, he possessedmore Olympic medalsthan 161 countries.  Phelps and his wife, Nicole Johnson, welcomed theirfourth child in October.  Peacockwill serve as the primary platform for NBC's coverage of the Olympic Games in Paris, which are scheduled for July 26 through Aug. 11.  NBC and Peacock will present live coverage of the 2024 Paris OlympicsOpening Ceremonyon Friday, July 26, beginning at noon ET | 9 a.m. PT. Telemundo will provide Spanish-language coverage beginning at 1 p.m. ET.  Primetime coverageis set to begin at 7:30 p.m. ET/PT on both NBC and Peacock.\"}"